# Unity Resource Guide

## Input

### Core APIs

[InputAction](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.InputAction.html)
- Represents a single action like jump, move, or attacke

[InputActionMap](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.InputActionMap.html)
- A grouping of InputActions
- Useful for switching control schemes based on game state (menu vs gameplay)

[PlayerInput](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.PlayerInput.html)
- Simplifies integrating iput with Unity events or message based systems

[InputValue](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.InputValue.html)
- Wrapper used in UnityEvents for getting input values

[InputControlScheme](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.InputControlScheme.html)
- Represents a control scheme like gamepad, keyboard & mouse

[InputSystem](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.InputSystem.html)
- Entry point for querying connected devices
- Can be useful for debugging device handling at runtime

## Useful APIs

[InputDevice](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.InputDevice.html)
- Base class for input hardware

[Gamepadhttps://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.Gamepad.html
- Has helpers for checking inputs manually

[Keyboard](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.Keyboard.html)
- For querying key presses

[Mouse](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.inputsystem@1.0/api/UnityEngine.InputSystem.Mouse.html)
 - For querying mouse clicks
